about where they

00:10:51.650 --> 00:10:54.830 align:middle line:84%
give birth, who'll look after
them, and the kind of birth

00:10:54.830 --> 00:10:56.060 align:middle line:90%
that they want.

00:10:56.060 --> 00:10:59.150 align:middle line:84%
>> This is an unusual
maternity service,

00:10:59.150 --> 00:11:02.450 align:middle line:84%
because we have about 5 and
1/2 thousand deliveries,

00:11:02.450 --> 00:11:05.390 align:middle line:84%
of which about
2,000, slightly less,

00:11:05.390 --> 00:11:09.350 align:middle line:84%
take place either at home
or in midwife-led units,

00:11:09.350 --> 00:11:12.620 align:middle line:84%
which most people in the
developed world would think was

00:11:12.620 --> 00:11:14.210 align:middle line:90%
either impossible or mad.

00:11:14.210 --> 00:11:17.760 align:middle line:84%
>> With home births,
it's just the gentleness.

00:11:17.760 --> 00:11:19.290 align:middle line:90%
It's the whole ambience.

00:11:19.290 --> 00:11:20.570 align:middle line:90%
You get the low lights.

00:11:20.570 --> 00:11:21.860 align:middle line:90%
You can have the candles.

00:11:21.860 --> 00:11:23.443 align:middle line:84%
They can eat and
drink when they want.

00:11:23.443 --> 00:11:24.860 align:middle line:90%
They can go to their own toilet.

00:11:24.860 --> 00:11:26.780 align:middle line:90%
They're with their family.

00:11:26.780 --> 00:11:29.210 align:middle line:84%
That is a lot when
you're in labor.

00:11:29.210 --> 00:11:32.060 align:middle line:84%
And you can have
the children there

00:11:32.060 --> 00:11:36.250 align:middle line:84%
if you want to have the children
there, the family members.

00:11:36.250 --> 00:11:37.270 align:middle line:90%
It's like a ritual.

00:11:37.270 --> 00:11:39.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The ball is very firmly
in the woman's court.

00:11:39.840 --> 00:11:40.830 align:middle line:90%
It's her home.

00:11:40.830 --> 00:11:41.630 align:middle line:90%
It's her domain.

00:11:41.630 --> 00:11:43.430 align:middle line:90%
>> She calls the shots.

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:45.680 align:middle line:84%
>> And you have to always
remember that you're a guest

00:11:45.680 --> 00:11:47.080 align:middle line:90%
in that home.

00:11:47.080 --> 00:11:49.208 align:middle line:84%
And so if she wants to
stop at 10 centimeters

00:11:49.208 --> 00:11:51.500 align:middle line:84%
and start cooking beans on
toast, then you have to say,

00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:53.337 align:middle line:84%
that's fine, as
long as I can listen

00:11:53.337 --> 00:11:54.670 align:middle line:90%
in to the baby for five minutes.

00:11:54.670 --> 00:11:55.472 align:middle line:90%
You carry on.

00:11:55.472 --> 00:11:58.490 align:middle line:84%
You obviously feel you
need beans on toast.

00:11:58.490 --> 00:12:01.220 align:middle line:84%
>> I may even go
put the coffee on.

00:12:01.220 --> 00:12:02.890 align:middle line:90%
>> It's very much their game.

00:12:02.890 --> 00:12:07.280 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, there are things
you have to do for safety.

00:12:07.280 --> 00:12:10.630 align:middle line:84%
But apart from that, there's
just very little-- everything's

00:12:10.630 --> 00:12:12.050 align:middle line:90%
very, very fluid.

00:12:12.050 --> 00:12:17.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Why would you not encourage
women to try and do the most

00:12:17.240 --> 00:12:21.800 align:middle line:84%
natural, beneficial thing
for them and their baby?

00:12:21.800 --> 00:12:24.140 align:middle line:84%
Why would you not
encourage them?

00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:25.760 align:middle line:90%
It's bizarre to me.

00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:27.560 align:middle line:84%
Why would you ignore
the statistics

00:12:27.560 --> 00:12:29.720 align:middle line:84%
from all the countries
where it is a natural thing

00:12:29.720 --> 00:12:30.860 align:middle line:90%
and it does happen?

00:12:30.860 --> 00:12:32.960 align:middle line:84%
Why would you say
that can't be right,

00:12:32.960 --> 00:12:35.270 align:middle line:84%
and it doesn't apply to
Australian women or women

00:12:35.270 --> 00:12:36.740 align:middle line:90%
living in this country?

00:12:36.740 --> 00:12:38.420 align:middle line:90%
What are we so afraid of?

00:12:38.420 --> 00:12:40.700 align:middle line:90%
I don't get it.

00:12:40.700 --> 00:12:42.710 align:middle line:84%
>> We've had a very large
home birth study from

00:12:42.710 --> 00:12:46.280 align:middle line:84%
the Netherlands, over 500,000
women giving birth there,

00:12:46.280 --> 00:12:47.600 align:middle line:90%
low-risk women with midwives.

00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:49.640 align:middle line:84%
No difference in
perinatal mortality

00:12:49.640 --> 00:12:51.380 align:middle line:90%
to giving birth in hospital.

00:12:51.380 --> 00:12:55.130 align:middle line:84%
We've had the US study showing
over 5,000 births at home,

00:12:55.130 --> 00:12:56.150 align:middle line:90%
low-risk.

00:12:56.150 --> 00:12:58.220 align:middle line:84%
No difference in
perinatal outcome,

00:12:58.220 --> 00:13:00.440 align:middle line:84%
far better outcomes
for mom and baby.

00:13:00.440 --> 00:13:02.570 align:middle line:84%
But we've also had
some studies coming out

00:13:02.570 --> 00:13:04.140 align:middle line:90%
where they've mixed the risk.

00:13:04.140 --> 00:13:06.830 align:middle line:84%
So we've had a study coming
out of the UK, which had

00:13:06.830 --> 00:13:08.760 align:middle line:90%
twins and breaches included.

00:13:08.760 --> 00:13:11.260 align:middle line:84%
We've had a study coming out
from South Australia that again

00:13:11.260 --> 00:13:13.240 align:middle line:90%
had high risk-women involved.

00:13:13.240 --> 00:13:15.460 align:middle line:84%
Again, when you remove the
high-risk women and only

00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:17.450 align:middle line:84%
looked at the low-risk,
no difference.

00:13:17.450 --> 00:13:20.920 align:middle line:84%
Add the high risk, yes,
there is increased risk.

00:13:20.920 --> 00:13:22.240 align:middle line:90%
This isn't rocket science.

00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:23.950 align:middle line:90%
It makes total sense.

00:13:23.950 --> 00:13:25.570 align:middle line:84%
If there are added
risks, then home

00:13:25.570 --> 00:13:29.380 align:middle line:84%
is not often the best
place to be physically.

00:13:29.380 --> 00:13:31.780 align:middle line:84%
But some women may
feel mentally it is.

00:13:31.780 --> 00:13:34.150 align:middle line:84%
And then we come to the
third part of the debate.

00:13:34.150 --> 00:13:35.935 align:middle line:84%
Do women have the
right to make a choice?

00:13:35.935 --> 00:13:39.500 align:middle line:90%


00:13:39.500 --> 00:13:44.233 align:middle line:84%
>> The definitive study where
you enroll a group of women

00:13:44.233 --> 00:13:46.400 align:middle line:84%
in home birth and a group
of women in hospital birth

00:13:46.400 --> 00:13:48.440 align:middle line:84%
and look at it,
it won't be done.

00:13:48.440 --> 00:13:49.610 align:middle line:90%
There'll always be biases.

00:13:49.610 --> 00:13:51.110 align:middle line:90%
That study won't be done.

00:13:51.110 --> 00:13:54.755 align:middle line:84%
So they have to be
done retrospectively,

00:13:54.755 --> 00:13:59.090 align:middle line:84%
where you look back at births
and the data surrounding it

00:13:59.090 --> 00:14:00.410 align:middle line:90%
and look at those figures.

00:14:00.410 --> 00:14:05.510 align:middle line:84%
And yes, each interest
group will obviously

00:14:05.510 --> 00:14:08.810 align:middle line:84%
be able to cite papers
and studies which support

00:14:08.810 --> 00:14:10.998 align:middle line:90%
their particular argument.

00:14:10.998 --> 00:14:13.040 align:middle line:84%
>> Having worked both in
the UK and in Australia,

00:14:13.040 --> 00:14:16.460 align:middle line:84%
one of the challenges in
Australia is that looking after

00:14:16.460 --> 00:14:20.420 align:middle line:84%
healthy pregnancies is the bread
and butter for a large section

00:14:20.420 --> 00:14:21.545 align:middle line:90%
of the obstetric workforce.

00:14:21.545 --> 00:14:23.420 align:middle line:84%
And it's difficult
to relinquish that.

00:14:23.420 --> 00:14:25.295 align:middle line:84%
It's not something you
can give up overnight.

00:14:25.295 --> 00:14:27.770 align:middle line:84%
It's a massive
industrial change.

00:14:27.770 --> 00:14:30.100 align:middle line:84%
That doesn't exist in the
UK under the National Health

00:14:30.100 --> 00:14:31.850 align:middle line:84%
Service, where
obstetricians actually want

00:14:31.850 --> 00:14:34.220 align:middle line:84%
to look after
complex pregnancies

00:14:34.220 --> 00:14:36.380 align:middle line:84%
and complicated
births only and are

00:14:36.380 --> 00:14:39.620 align:middle line:84%
very happy to leave the
normal healthy pregnancies

00:14:39.620 --> 00:14:42.035 align:middle line:90%
to midwives or to GPs.

00:14:42.035 --> 00:14:43.160 align:middle line:90%
And I think that's healthy.

00:14:43.160 --> 00:14:45.550 align:middle line:84%
And if we were honest,
if we stood back from it,

00:14:45.550 --> 00:14:47.300 align:middle line:84%
that's probably in the
interests of women.

00:14:47.300 --> 00:14:49.795 align:middle line:90%
