outcomes.

00:15:29.635 --> 00:15:30.510 align:middle line:90%
Everybody knows this.

00:15:30.510 --> 00:15:32.860 align:middle line:84%
And there's hard
research to prove it.

00:15:32.860 --> 00:15:37.590 align:middle line:84%
But the system really doesn't
necessarily reflect that.

00:15:37.590 --> 00:15:39.450 align:middle line:90%
They don't make that a priority.

00:15:39.450 --> 00:15:42.455 align:middle line:84%
>> Of course, it's not
just about continuity,

00:15:42.455 --> 00:15:44.580 align:middle line:84%
because you can't continuity
of care from a medical

00:15:44.580 --> 00:15:45.270 align:middle line:90%
professional.

00:15:45.270 --> 00:15:47.040 align:middle line:84%
And they will take a
very medical attitude

00:15:47.040 --> 00:15:53.280 align:middle line:84%
and still very much see you as
a belly, a baby, blood pressure,

00:15:53.280 --> 00:15:54.180 align:middle line:90%
et cetera.

00:15:54.180 --> 00:15:57.360 align:middle line:84%
Continuity care from a midwifery
perspective is a social model.

00:15:57.360 --> 00:16:00.330 align:middle line:84%
And that involves how are
you going as a person.

00:16:00.330 --> 00:16:02.610 align:middle line:84%
It involves listening
a lot, talking a lot.

00:16:02.610 --> 00:16:04.440 align:middle line:90%
It involves empowering women.

00:16:04.440 --> 00:16:05.615 align:middle line:90%
Of course, you can do this.

00:16:05.615 --> 00:16:06.990 align:middle line:84%
Your body is
designed to do this.

00:16:06.990 --> 00:16:09.870 align:middle line:84%
It involves women
actually helping women

00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:11.360 align:middle line:90%
to believe in themselves.

00:16:11.360 --> 00:16:16.810 align:middle line:84%
>> With both births, I didn't
do much visiting of doctors.

00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:19.830 align:middle line:84%
I went to a doctor for
confirmation of the pregnancy

00:16:19.830 --> 00:16:22.410 align:middle line:84%
and expressed my desire
to have a home birth

00:16:22.410 --> 00:16:26.150 align:middle line:84%
