She said to me, oh, no.

00:59:22.983 --> 00:59:24.900 align:middle line:84%
We have to get that
placenta out straightaway.

00:59:24.900 --> 00:59:26.530 align:middle line:84%
I always cut the cord and
then take the thing out,

00:59:26.530 --> 00:59:29.120 align:middle line:84%
because my job's not done till
I can inspect the placenta.

00:59:29.120 --> 00:59:33.310 align:middle line:84%
Her job's not done till she
can inspect the placenta.

00:59:33.310 --> 00:59:36.210 align:middle line:84%
So she can't wait around
40 minutes for me?

00:59:36.210 --> 00:59:38.960 align:middle line:90%


00:59:38.960 --> 00:59:42.330 align:middle line:90%
So it made me very upset.

00:59:42.330 --> 00:59:45.000 align:middle line:84%
>> How often have we all
seen obstetricians sort

00:59:45.000 --> 00:59:50.180 align:middle line:84%
of fidgeting, wanting this
baby out, that sort of thing?

00:59:50.180 --> 00:59:53.600 align:middle line:84%
That's not really quite
what it's all about.

00:59:53.600 --> 00:59:56.000 align:middle line:84%
Midwives, on the other hand,
are there for the duration.

00:59:56.000 --> 00:59:57.500 align:middle line:90%
They have nothing else to do.

00:59:57.500 --> 01:00:02.570 align:middle line:84%
That is their focus, boing, you
are going to have your baby.

01:00:02.570 --> 01:00:04.940 align:middle line:84%
And I'm going to be with
you until you've delivered.

01:00:04.940 --> 01:00:07.640 align:middle line:84%
And if it's in 10
minutes, whoopee.

01:00:07.640 --> 01:00:12.080 align:middle line:84%
If it's in three hours
and 47 minutes, so be it.

01:00:12.080 --> 01:00:15.260 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
sort of attendant,

01:00:15.260 --> 01:00:17.190 align:middle line:84%
it seems to me,
that somebody needs

01:00:17.190 --> 01:00:21.110 align:middle line:84%
in childbirth, and
absolutely not somebody who's

01:00:21.110 --> 01:00:23.270 align:middle line:90%
got other things to do.

01:00:23.270 --> 01:00:25.640 align:middle line:84%
Now, it may be that
out there, there

01:00:25.640 --> 01:00:27.830 align:middle line:84%
is a massive cohort
of obstetricians

01:00:27.830 --> 01:00:30.200 align:middle line:84%
who are prepared to
take exactly that view.

01:00:30.200 --> 01:00:34.070 align:middle line:84%
But I have to say,
haven't met them yet.

01:00:34.070 --> 01:00:37.980 align:middle line:84%
>> I just said, I don't
think this is going to work.

01:00:37.980 --> 01:00:39.640 align:middle line:90%
I think I have to go.

01:00:39.640 --> 01:00:41.390 align:middle line:84%
And the one thing I'll
give her credit for

01:00:41.390 --> 01:00:43.818 align:middle line:84%
is she recognized it wasn't
going to work as well.

01:00:43.818 --> 01:00:45.360 align:middle line:84%
And she didn't try
to talk me around.

01:00:45.360 --> 01:00:47.150 align:middle line:84%
She just went, yeah, I don't
think is going to work.

01:00:47.150 --> 01:00:48.983 align:middle line:84%
Mind you, she didn't
recommend anybody else.

01:00:48.983 --> 01:00:50.940 align:middle line:84%
So I walked out of there
at 36 weeks pregnant.

01:00:50.940 --> 01:00:54.400 align:middle line:90%
I had nowhere to have my baby.

01:00:54.400 --> 01:00:58.000 align:middle line:84%
>> The important thing is
that a woman births her baby

01:00:58.000 --> 01:01:01.480 align:middle line:84%
in an environment
that is good for her.

01:01:01.480 --> 01:01:03.760 align:middle line:90%
So she needs to feel supported.

01:01:03.760 --> 01:01:10.110 align:middle line:84%
She needs to feel safe, warm,
protected, comfortable, free

01:01:10.110 --> 01:01:11.520 align:middle line:90%
to move around.

01:01:11.520 --> 01:01:15.270 align:middle line:84%
She needs to feel at one
with the environment.

01:01:15.270 --> 01:01:18.990 align:middle line:84%
Now, for some women, the
very idea of home birth

01:01:18.990 --> 01:01:20.640 align:middle line:90%
would set them into a panic.

01:01:20.640 --> 01:01:22.188 align:middle line:84%
They associate
hospital with being

01:01:22.188 --> 01:01:23.730 align:middle line:84%
in a very safe place
where everything

01:01:23.730 --> 01:01:25.890 align:middle line:90%
is there to sort things out.

01:01:25.890 --> 01:01:28.310 align:middle line:84%
And that's fine
because that probably

01:01:28.310 --> 01:01:30.880 align:middle line:84%
will be the best
environment for them.

01:01:30.880 --> 01:01:33.960 align:middle line:84%
But as we know, a lot of
people don't like hospitals.

01:01:33.960 --> 01:01:35.430 align:middle line:90%
They associate it with illness.

01:01:35.430 --> 01:01:38.400 align:middle line:84%
And they don't like
the smell even.

01:01:38.400 --> 01:01:40.210 align:middle line:84%
They don't like
anything about it.

01:01:40.210 --> 01:01:41.910 align:middle line:84%
And it starts to
sense that's not

01:01:41.910 --> 01:01:45.360 align:middle line:84%
going to be a great place
for them to labor and birth.

01:01:45.360 --> 01:01:48.480 align:middle line:84%
>> To me, having a room full
of medical professionals

01:01:48.480 --> 01:01:51.420 align:middle line:84%
at my birth, I see
that as empowering.

01:01:51.420 --> 01:01:54.990 align:middle line:84%
I see myself as being lucky
and fortunate to have that.

01:01:54.990 --> 01:01:57.670 align:middle line:84%
I don't see it as
a bad thing at all.

01:01:57.670 --> 01:01:59.520 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I see it
is a great thing.

01:01:59.520 --> 01:02:01.530 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, the thought
of actually having a baby

01:02:01.530 --> 01:02:04.020 align:middle line:84%
in hospital makes me
feel physically ill.

01:02:04.020 --> 01:02:05.757 align:middle line:84%
Even visiting friends
of mine in hospital

01:02:05.757 --> 01:02:08.340 align:middle line:84%
after they've had their babies,
just the rules and the routine

01:02:08.340 --> 01:02:10.510 align:middle line:84%
and everything, even that
will set my teeth on edge.

01:02:10.510 --> 01:02:15.710 align:middle line:84%
Whereas being at home, you're
just free to be who you are.

01:02:15.710 --> 01:02:20.780 align:middle line:84%
>> Walking into the Hawthorne
birth center and meeting

01:02:20.780 --> 01:02:25.100 align:middle line:84%
Barbara the midwife and Bruce,
it was just like I didn't have

01:02:25.100 --> 01:02:26.420 align:middle line:90%
to worry about that anymore.

01:02:26.420 --> 01:02:31.190 align:middle line:84%
So I could just be in the space
I needed to be to have Olivia.

01:02:31.190 --> 01:02:34.430 align:middle line:90%


01:02:34.430 --> 01:02:39.020 align:middle line:84%
I went into labor
in the late evening.

01:02:39.020 --> 01:02:39.860 align:middle line:90%
I'd gone to bed.

01:02:39.860 --> 01:02:42.542 align:middle line:90%
And I woke up with labor pains.

01:02:42.542 --> 01:02:44.000 align:middle line:84%
And my sister had
stayed the night.

01:02:44.000 --> 01:02:45.170 align:middle line:90%
And Matt was there.

01:02:45.170 --> 01:02:46.740 align:middle line:90%
And we rang the midwife.

01:02:46.740 --> 01:02:50.620 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I'll go to the
birth center and put Paul on.

01:02:50.620 --> 01:02:52.160 align:middle line:90%
And she did that.

01:02:52.160 --> 01:02:54.770 align:middle line:84%
I actually got in
the bath at home,

01:02:54.770 --> 01:02:56.460 align:middle line:84%
because water was
very important to me.

01:02:56.460 --> 01:02:59.744 align:middle line:90%
I knew I wanted water around me.

01:02:59.744 --> 01:03:01.880 align:middle line:84%
I labored at home
not for very long.

01:03:01.880 --> 01:03:05.100 align:middle line:84%
And I'd gone into established
labor quite quickly.

01:03:05.100 --> 01:03:05.900 align:middle line:90%
We got in the car.

01:03:05.900 --> 01:03:06.970 align:middle line:90%
That was the worst bit.

01:03:06.970 --> 01:03:08.637 align:middle line:84%
It's really shitty
getting in a car when

01:03:08.637 --> 01:03:11.810 align:middle line:84%
you're in labor because
you go out of your home

01:03:11.810 --> 01:03:14.750 align:middle line:90%
into traffic and noise and dark.

01:03:14.750 --> 01:03:16.265 align:middle line:90%
And you can't get comfortable.

01:03:16.265 --> 01:03:17.630 align:middle line:90%
And that was yucky.

01:03:17.630 --> 01:03:19.255 align:middle line:84%
So then when I got
to the birth center,

01:03:19.255 --> 01:03:21.540 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to get in
the water straight away.

01:03:21.540 --> 01:03:24.010 align:middle line:90%
I labored in the water.

01:03:24.010 --> 01:03:28.160 align:middle line:84%
And when this involuntary
muscle contraction happened,

01:03:28.160 --> 01:03:29.410 align:middle line:90%
something went off in my hand.

01:03:29.410 --> 01:03:34.165 align:middle line:90%
And I went, aha, OK, I get it.

01:03:34.165 --> 01:03:36.820 align:middle line:90%
Then I went into second stage.

01:03:36.820 --> 01:03:41.120 align:middle line:84%
And when I got the pushing
urge, I was like, oh, right,

01:03:41.120 --> 01:03:42.030 align:middle line:90%
that bearing down.

01:03:42.030 --> 01:03:44.122 align:middle line:84%
And so the only way
that I can describe--

01:03:44.122 --> 01:03:46.330 align:middle line:84%
and this isn't a medical
description, you understand.

01:03:46.330 --> 01:03:48.280 align:middle line:84%
This is a Kate
Gorman description.

01:03:48.280 --> 01:03:54.460 align:middle line:84%
Is your uterus is doing this
and pushing down and pushing in.

01:03:54.460 --> 01:03:56.350 align:middle line:84%
And you can use
your stomach muscles

01:03:56.350 --> 01:03:58.900 align:middle line:84%
to do that as well
in the same time.

01:03:58.900 --> 01:04:01.450 align:middle line:84%
And once I got that it
was like I had something.

01:04:01.450 --> 01:04:02.920 align:middle line:90%
I knew what to do.

01:04:02.920 --> 01:04:05.490 align:middle line:90%
And I was like, oh, I'm fine.

01:04:05.490 --> 01:04:07.750 align:middle line:90%
I remember feeling the head.

01:04:07.750 --> 01:04:09.100 align:middle line:90%
And it actually was coming out.

01:04:09.100 --> 01:04:10.570 align:middle line:90%
And just, oh, my god.

01:04:10.570 --> 01:04:11.980 align:middle line:90%
My baby's coming.

01:04:11.980 --> 01:04:13.510 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I'm so excited.

01:04:13.510 --> 01:04:16.420 align:middle line:90%
It was just beautiful.

01:04:16.420 --> 01:04:20.180 align:middle line:90%
And I was doing it.

01:04:20.180 --> 01:04:24.930 align:middle line:84%
Then when Olivia was born in
the water, Matt caught her.

01:04:24.930 --> 01:04:28.030 align:middle line:90%
He was sitting behind me.

01:04:28.030 --> 01:04:30.430 align:middle line:84%
And he passed her
up through my legs.

01:04:30.430 --> 01:04:32.890 align:middle line:84%
And I brought her up
through the water.

01:04:32.890 --> 01:04:36.720 align:middle line:84%
And Barbara gave
me a face washer.

01:04:36.720 --> 01:04:38.660 align:middle line:84%
And she said, Kate,
just wipe her face.

01:04:38.660 --> 01:04:39.490 align:middle line:90%
I wiped her face.

01:04:39.490 --> 01:04:41.350 align:middle line:90%
I went, [BLOWS SOFTLY].

01:04:41.350 --> 01:04:45.129 align:middle line:90%
And she went, [GASPS HAPPILY].

01:04:45.129 --> 01:04:46.560 align:middle line:90%
[CHUCKLES]

01:04:46.560 --> 01:04:49.430 align:middle line:90%


01:04:49.430 --> 01:04:53.360 align:middle line:84%
And it was like
giving life again.

01:04:53.360 --> 01:04:55.000 align:middle line:90%
I'd just given birth.

01:04:55.000 --> 01:04:58.896 align:middle line:90%
And then I made her breathe.

01:04:58.896 --> 01:05:01.356 align:middle line:90%
