01:05:01.356 --> 01:05:06.753 align:middle line:90%


01:05:06.753 --> 01:05:09.170 align:middle line:84%
>> So there is something about
the template about birthing

01:05:09.170 --> 01:05:11.503 align:middle line:84%
and taking it on and going
through that rite of passage,

01:05:11.503 --> 01:05:15.125 align:middle line:84%
having the support around that
helps you to move through that

01:05:15.125 --> 01:05:19.780 align:middle line:84%
that sets a pattern in the
mother at least and I think

01:05:19.780 --> 01:05:23.810 align:middle line:84%
for the partners to feel
like with the right support,

01:05:23.810 --> 01:05:24.947 align:middle line:90%
I can take on anything.

01:05:24.947 --> 01:05:27.530 align:middle line:84%
And with the right support, my
own strength will come forward.

01:05:27.530 --> 01:05:30.480 align:middle line:84%
And this is a fabulous place
to be starting our parenting

01:05:30.480 --> 01:05:31.280 align:middle line:90%
journey from.

01:05:31.280 --> 01:05:38.615 align:middle line:90%


01:05:38.615 --> 01:05:42.230 align:middle line:84%
>> In my second pregnancy,
circumstances had us living

01:05:42.230 --> 01:05:43.620 align:middle line:90%
in England.

01:05:43.620 --> 01:05:44.420 align:middle line:90%
We were on a farm.

01:05:44.420 --> 01:05:46.480 align:middle line:84%
But there was a small
village near us.

01:05:46.480 --> 01:05:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And it had a clinic,
a doctors' clinic.

01:05:49.890 --> 01:05:53.990 align:middle line:84%
And attached to that was
a midwifery department.

01:05:53.990 --> 01:05:58.000 align:middle line:84%
I was walking into NHS
expecting a bit of a fight.

01:05:58.000 --> 01:06:01.420 align:middle line:84%
And I knew what I wanted
was a water birth at home.

01:06:01.420 --> 01:06:02.960 align:middle line:90%
They didn't blink an eyelid.

01:06:02.960 --> 01:06:05.600 align:middle line:90%
It happens all the time.

01:06:05.600 --> 01:06:09.950 align:middle line:84%
In my little tiny area,
they do one a month.

01:06:09.950 --> 01:06:13.580 align:middle line:84%
>> It felt so good to be
in a maternity system where

01:06:13.580 --> 01:06:15.740 align:middle line:90%
my choices were supported.

01:06:15.740 --> 01:06:18.350 align:middle line:84%
And I was surrounded
by midwives who

01:06:18.350 --> 01:06:20.490 align:middle line:90%
knew that home birth was safe.

01:06:20.490 --> 01:06:22.980 align:middle line:84%
I just find it so
frustrating that Australia

01:06:22.980 --> 01:06:23.980 align:middle line:90%
doesn't think like that.

01:06:23.980 --> 01:06:26.940 align:middle line:90%


01:06:26.940 --> 01:06:29.660 align:middle line:84%
>> It's interesting for me to
travel to so many countries

01:06:29.660 --> 01:06:34.370 align:middle line:84%
of the world and to see how
many countries are imitating US

01:06:34.370 --> 01:06:40.313 align:middle line:84%
maternity care policy
when it's not a good idea.

01:06:40.313 --> 01:06:41.480 align:middle line:90%
And you can like blue jeans.

01:06:41.480 --> 01:06:42.320 align:middle line:90%
You can like jazz.

01:06:42.320 --> 01:06:45.230 align:middle line:84%
But don't like our
maternity care policies,

01:06:45.230 --> 01:06:48.740 align:middle line:84%
because they're not
leading you in a good way.

01:06:48.740 --> 01:06:51.620 align:middle line:84%
>> The maternity care system
in New Zealand, in my opinion,

01:06:51.620 --> 01:06:53.060 align:middle line:90%
is the best in the world.

01:06:53.060 --> 01:06:55.190 align:middle line:84%
I used to think the
Netherlands was the best.

01:06:55.190 --> 01:06:57.260 align:middle line:84%
And now I would
rate it number two.

01:06:57.260 --> 01:06:58.980 align:middle line:84%
But New Zealand I
would rate number one.

01:06:58.980 --> 01:06:59.780 align:middle line:90%
Why?

01:06:59.780 --> 01:07:03.440 align:middle line:84%
Because first of all,
100% of New Zealand births

01:07:03.440 --> 01:07:04.910 align:middle line:90%
are attended by midwives.

01:07:04.910 --> 01:07:08.550 align:middle line:84%
Second of all, a mother
has her full choice

01:07:08.550 --> 01:07:10.160 align:middle line:90%
to pick a lead maternity carer.

01:07:10.160 --> 01:07:11.360 align:middle line:90%
They call it LMC.

01:07:11.360 --> 01:07:13.580 align:middle line:90%
And that can be a midwife.

01:07:13.580 --> 01:07:14.810 align:middle line:90%
It can be an obstetrician.

01:07:14.810 --> 01:07:16.730 align:middle line:90%
Or it can be a GP.

01:07:16.730 --> 01:07:20.935 align:middle line:84%
Well, when the midwives
set this up in the 1990s,

01:07:20.935 --> 01:07:22.310 align:middle line:84%
obstetricians went
along with it,

01:07:22.310 --> 01:07:25.580 align:middle line:84%
because they thought the lead
maternity carer would be them.

01:07:25.580 --> 01:07:28.310 align:middle line:84%
Ironically enough, 80%
of New Zealand women

01:07:28.310 --> 01:07:31.340 align:middle line:84%
pick a midwife to be their
lead maternity carer.

01:07:31.340 --> 01:07:32.900 align:middle line:84%
Now, New Zealand
midwives are all

01:07:32.900 --> 01:07:35.030 align:middle line:84%
about normal
physiological birth.

01:07:35.030 --> 01:07:36.830 align:middle line:84%
It's the model that
they're taught.

01:07:36.830 --> 01:07:38.792 align:middle line:84%
And all their skills
in school, what

01:07:38.792 --> 01:07:40.250 align:middle line:84%
they learn in
midwifery training is

01:07:40.250 --> 01:07:43.280 align:middle line:84%
how to facilitate normal
physiological birth.

01:07:43.280 --> 01:07:46.460 align:middle line:84%
>> If you look at the reforms
around birth in New Zealand--

01:07:46.460 --> 01:07:52.100 align:middle line:84%
and we were all in much the
same position 20 years ago.

01:07:52.100 --> 01:07:56.360 align:middle line:84%
0.3% of women gave birth
at home at that time.

01:07:56.360 --> 01:07:58.460 align:middle line:90%
And we're still there.

01:07:58.460 --> 01:08:01.580 align:middle line:84%
But in New Zealand, they
had a visionary woman

01:08:01.580 --> 01:08:03.350 align:middle line:84%
who was the health
minister who later

01:08:03.350 --> 01:08:05.130 align:middle line:90%
became the prime minister.

01:08:05.130 --> 01:08:08.420 align:middle line:84%
Her whole cabinet, every
woman in that parliament

01:08:08.420 --> 01:08:12.830 align:middle line:84%
crossed the floor
to vote that women

01:08:12.830 --> 01:08:17.420 align:middle line:84%
should have the choice of where
to give birth and with whom.

01:08:17.420 --> 01:08:19.550 align:middle line:90%
And it was as simple as that.

01:08:19.550 --> 01:08:23.600 align:middle line:84%
>> If a woman goes to a
midwife in British Columbia,

01:08:23.600 --> 01:08:26.660 align:middle line:90%
she is cared for by the midwife.

01:08:26.660 --> 01:08:28.600 align:middle line:84%
But the midwife
bills the government.

01:08:28.600 --> 01:08:33.859 align:middle line:84%
So the provincial medical
health care system actually

01:08:33.859 --> 01:08:38.060 align:middle line:84%
compensates, pays the midwife
for the care that she provides.

01:08:38.060 --> 01:08:42.439 align:middle line:84%
So having a home birth as
part of the health care system

01:08:42.439 --> 01:08:48.020 align:middle line:84%
is actually a safety factor
as well as a social factor.

01:08:48.020 --> 01:08:51.260 align:middle line:84%
>> I think women who choose
to have a home birth deserve

01:08:51.260 --> 01:08:55.069 align:middle line:84%
government support, just
as I received some sort

01:08:55.069 --> 01:08:57.960 align:middle line:84%
